'''''Prefatory Remarks on Prose Translation of 'Beowulf'''''' is a preface written by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] for [[John R. Clark Hall]]'s book ''[[Beowulf and the Finnsburg Fragment]]'', published in [[1940]]. It was reprinted as "'''On Translating Beowulf'''" in ''[[The Monsters and the Critics and Other Essays]]'' (1983).

In the section "On Metre", Tolkien quotes 19 lines from his own alliterative translation of ''[[Beowulf]]'' (''[[The Tale of Beewolf Son of Echgethew]]'') to explain the metre of the poem. More portions from this work were published in [[2024]] as no. 88 of ''[[The Collected Poems of J.R.R. Tolkien]]''.

